com.iland.core.api.security

Enum Permission

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Permission>
      • com.iland.core.api.security.Permission
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Permission>

    public enum Permission
extends Enum<Permission>
    Permissions Enum. This is the set of permissions that we use to secure our API. We define the entity type so that we can associate each permission with the appropriate entity. We define the permission type so that we can determine whether read-only users should have access to certain endpoints.
    Author:
    Cory Snyder
